OL,6,F"One minute you're conscious, you're
OL,7,Ftalking. You take it and it's not till
OL,8,Fyou come round with people gathered
OL,9,Fround you, or you wake up in hospital,
OL,10,Fthat you realise what's happened."
OL,12,FScott credits a treatment called
OL,13,FNaloxone for saving his life. Produced
OL,14,Fas both an injection and a nasal
OL,15,Fspray, it rapidly reverses the affects
OL,16,Fof an opioid overdose. The Scottish
OL,17,FGovernment launched a national scheme
OL,18,Frolling it out across the country in
OL,19,F2011, and say they continue to
OL,20,Fencourage health boards to embed it
OL,21,Fwithin local areas.
